    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="117"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d117">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72111/1930</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">21 April, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I am glad to accept the
                    emendations suggested (except where I have run my pencil through them) and also
                    the rearrangement of paragraphs, and hasten to return the note to be copied and
                        delivered.<note n="25" xml:id="d117fn1">For text of the note as sent, see
                            <ref target="frus1915Supp#pg_160">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1915, supp., p.
                        160</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I took advantage of your suggestion to add the words (p. 6) “and I respectfully
                    submit that none of the circumstances urged in Your Excellency’s memorandum
                    alters the principle involved.”<note n="26" xml:id="d117fn2">
                        <ref target="frus1915Supp#pg_160">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 162</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>In haste,</p>
                <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. W.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
